as it has in other rooms.

1082
00:42:45,679 --> 00:42:47,360
No, I think we keep going.

1083
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:48,199
You carry forward.

1084
00:42:48,199 --> 00:42:49,119
It feels like something's happening.

1085
00:42:49,119 --> 00:42:51,279
We don't know what it is, but something.

1086
00:42:51,279 --> 00:42:53,480
You carry forward, the echoes continue

1087
00:42:53,519 --> 00:42:56,280
through the halls as you walk down them.

1088
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,320
You get feelings that you're being watched

1089
00:42:58,320 --> 00:43:00,519
or followed, but every time you turn around

1090
00:43:00,519 --> 00:43:04,159
and wait or move to go towards them

1091
00:43:04,159 --> 00:43:08,440
in either area, the big world or the small world,

1092
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:11,440
you don't see anything.

1093
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:13,760
You carry on in other ways

1094
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:18,760
and you get to the end of a long hallway

1095
00:43:19,760 --> 00:43:23,920
and you come up to a door.

1096
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:28,400
There's no light under this door

1097
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:30,800
or none that you can see anyways.

1098
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:36,680
And on the door, you see that the slate,

1099
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:41,280
the pelvic bone, and what looks like a spine

1100
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:46,040
now carved into this doorway in front of you.

1101
00:43:46,199 --> 00:43:50,559
Yeah, I guess Team Real World opens up the door.

1102
00:43:50,559 --> 00:43:54,159
You open the door, Flint and Mannix, Yenbul and Thea.

1103
00:43:54,159 --> 00:43:56,320
Thea had a marker outstretched

1104
00:43:56,320 --> 00:43:58,599
and was just about to draw a penis

1105
00:43:59,519 --> 00:44:00,840
on it when the door opened

1106
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:03,599
and she's like, ah, missed opportunity.

1107
00:44:03,599 --> 00:44:07,480
Door opens before you and inside you see,

1108
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:12,039
and you do see a room very similar to the one previous.

1109
00:44:12,039 --> 00:44:15,519
There's the carvings, circular carvings on the floor.

1110
00:44:16,279 --> 00:44:20,079
But it's illuminated by a black,

1111
00:44:20,079 --> 00:44:22,440
almost super dark purple light.

1112
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:25,320
So the room isn't super well lit.

1113
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:28,719
And it's coming from this black looking crystal

1114
00:44:28,719 --> 00:44:30,320
in the middle of the room.

1115
00:44:31,519 --> 00:44:32,679
This one looks creepy.

1116
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:37,880
I'm going to go in my bag and find something white

1117
00:44:37,880 --> 00:44:39,840
to see if it glows in this light.

1118
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:44,079
Maybe some sort of psychedelic mushroom poster.

1119
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:45,759
Yeah, I like that.

1120
00:44:45,759 --> 00:44:49,360
It glows, the iridescence of it.

1121
00:44:49,360 --> 00:44:53,960
You even see it just faintly in the big world.

1122
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:54,799
That's cool.

1123
00:44:56,119 --> 00:44:58,159
Have you been carrying that poster in this entire time?

1124
00:44:58,159 --> 00:45:01,039
Yes, well, when everything went so bad in Calumport,

1125
00:45:01,039 --> 00:45:02,599
I was on my way to get it framed

1126
00:45:02,599 --> 00:45:06,599
for my cool psychedelic room at my house.

1127
00:45:06,599 --> 00:45:08,239
That's awesome.

1128
00:45:08,239 --> 00:45:10,039
Maybe if it is not destroyed,

1129
00:45:10,039 --> 00:45:11,440
I will take you there one day.

1130
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:12,400
That'd be great.

1131
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:13,480
You know what?

1132
00:45:13,519 --> 00:45:15,519
We should hang this poster in this room.

1133
00:45:17,159 --> 00:45:19,800
You're right, a little, we were here present

1134
00:45:20,679 --> 00:45:22,599
for Shangri-La.

1135
00:45:22,599 --> 00:45:24,440
I mean, he won't be able to fully enjoy it

1136
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:26,480
because we're totally gonna take that crystal,

1137
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:27,800
but yeah.

1138
00:45:29,599 --> 00:45:31,000
You look up into the big world

1139
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:33,840
and you see Flint and Mannix staring down at you.

1140
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:36,559
They see us.

1141
00:45:36,559 --> 00:45:38,199
They see little.

1142
00:45:38,199 --> 00:45:39,639
Just like laughing.

1143
00:45:39,639 --> 00:45:42,760
A little poster, they're laughing.

1144
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:43,760
Now it's up on the wall.

1145
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:45,600
It's back and forth.

1146
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,240
And then a poster appears on the wall,

1147
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:48,440
if that's where you put it.

1148
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:51,000
It's glowing with all, it's like,

1149
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:55,480
all the lines and all the colors are illuminated

1150
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:57,640
by this light that's being emitted.

1151
00:45:57,640 --> 00:45:59,320
I look at Mannix and I say,

1152
00:45:59,320 --> 00:46:02,640
well, this one's, I guess,

1153
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:05,720
a little different than the rest, but same idea.

1154
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:12,080
I guess so shall I take it.

1155
00:46:12,239 --> 00:46:14,079
Well, I mean, everyone else already has one.

1156
00:46:14,079 --> 00:46:15,840
So, sure.

1157
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:17,679
Who knows how many of these things there are.

1158
00:46:17,679 --> 00:46:18,519
Right.

1159
00:46:19,319 --> 00:46:20,400
Okay.

1160
00:46:20,400 --> 00:46:24,079
He grabs a bag and begins moving towards the crystal

1161
00:46:24,079 --> 00:46:26,000
and puts it over top.

1162
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,159
And it disappears for Yen Bull and Thea

1163
00:46:28,159 --> 00:46:30,519
and goes into the bag for Mannix.

1164
00:46:30,519 --> 00:46:35,079
He feels a pulse or pressure on his wrists

1165
00:46:35,079 --> 00:46:39,199
and looks down, says, did you get one of these?

1166
00:46:39,199 --> 00:46:41,719
I did, I have an idea.

1167
00:46:41,760 --> 00:46:44,480
And I hold out my bag with the dollar sign on it

1168
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:47,120
to like switch bags with him.

1169
00:46:48,120 --> 00:46:49,520
Okay.

1170
00:46:49,520 --> 00:46:52,880
He passes it to you, you pass.

1171
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:56,560
So he has the green one, you have the black one.

1172
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:57,400
Yeah.

1173
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:04,360
The tattoos on your wrist morph color before your eye

1174
00:47:04,360 --> 00:47:07,560
as you grab and hold onto the bags for a second.

1175
00:47:07,560 --> 00:47:09,040
So they change entirely.

1176
00:47:09,040 --> 00:47:10,560
It's not like I get a second one.

1177
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:11,600
Yes.

1178
00:47:11,599 --> 00:47:12,440
Okay.

1179
00:47:14,079 --> 00:47:15,360
Hmm.

1180
00:47:15,360 --> 00:47:16,759
Interesting.

1181
00:47:16,759 --> 00:47:19,519
I guess, switch back.

1182
00:47:19,519 --> 00:47:21,639
I am kind of attached to that bag

1183
00:47:21,639 --> 00:47:23,159
with the dollar sign on it.

1184
00:47:23,159 --> 00:47:24,360
It was a gift, you know.

1185
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:25,480
Sure, yes, of course.

1186
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:29,440
He hands it back to you, takes back the black one.

1187
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:30,880
Is there a new door?

1188
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:32,360
Did anything else weird happen

1189
00:47:32,360 --> 00:47:33,920
other than that this was a black one?

1190
00:47:33,920 --> 00:47:36,239
I will say this conversation was quick.

1191
00:47:36,239 --> 00:47:39,079
And as the gem is taken,

1192
00:47:39,079 --> 00:47:40,759
this quick exchange is happening,

1193
00:47:41,080 --> 00:47:42,800
Oh wait, Russ, can I try one more thing?

1194
00:47:42,800 --> 00:47:44,000
Yeah, sure, go for it.

1195
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:47,000
Can I have both of the bags?

1196
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:49,800
Sure, yes.

1197
00:47:49,800 --> 00:47:53,000
He hands you back the bag carrying the black gem

1198
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,360
and on your wrists,

1199
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:57,800
almost like they're piled on top of each other,

1200
00:47:57,800 --> 00:47:59,640
there's a green and a black gem.

1201
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:02,400
Huh.

1202
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:04,080
What do you see?

1203
00:48:04,080 --> 00:48:07,080
Mannix looks down to his wrist and says, mine's gone.

1204
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:09,280
I mean, I have both now.

1205
00:48:11,400 --> 00:48:12,960
Interesting.

1206
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:13,800
What are they doing up there?

1207
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:15,600
They're just passing bags back and forth.

1208
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:16,840
I know, we have been down here.

1209
00:48:16,840 --> 00:48:18,080
We put up a poster.

1210
00:48:18,080 --> 00:48:21,920
All they had to do was just grab the crystal.

1211
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:22,760
I don't know.

1212
00:48:23,680 --> 00:48:24,880
At least you get a little break.

1213
00:48:24,880 --> 00:48:26,440
I know you were tired.

1214
00:48:26,440 --> 00:48:30,120
Thanks for carrying me that few minutes there.

1215
00:48:30,120 --> 00:48:31,480
It's slower this time,

1216
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:34,360
but a door does slowly begin to appear

1217
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:38,240
and there's a bright light

1218
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:43,240
that comes from it as it's appearing on this wall.

1219
00:48:43,240 --> 00:48:46,000
Yeah, I'll hand his black one back to him

1220
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:48,720
just because it doesn't make sense for me to have both.

1221
00:48:49,760 --> 00:48:50,600
Or does it?

1222
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:51,440
I don't know.

1223
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:52,280
Who knows?

1224
00:48:52,280 --> 00:48:53,120
Who knows?

1225
00:48:53,120 --> 00:48:54,040
I have no idea.

1226
00:48:54,040 --> 00:48:55,360
Okay, you hand it back to Mannix

1227
00:48:55,360 --> 00:48:59,240
and he looks down and the tattoo reappears on his wrist.

1228
00:48:59,240 --> 00:49:02,000
The doorway slowly begins to appear.

1229
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,280
It took longer than it did in the last few rooms,

1230
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:07,240
but there's almost like bright golden light

1231
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:09,880
that is coming from behind it now.

1232
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:12,000
Ooh, this one's pretty.

1233
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:13,480
For a moment, I've almost forgotten

1234
00:49:13,480 --> 00:49:18,480
that we're in a lich's flying pyramid of doom.

1235
00:49:18,480 --> 00:49:21,560
I know, it seems like we are just on a fun adventure,

1236
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:26,000
not fighting for death to save my beloved homeland.

1237
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:29,720
All right, Thea opens the shiny door.

1238
00:49:29,720 --> 00:49:31,560
You open the door, Flint and Mannix,

1239
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:34,400
the door opens before you.

1240
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:38,200
And as the door cracks open,

1241
00:49:39,360 --> 00:49:44,360
inside there is a hideous cacophony of sounds,

1242
00:49:49,119 --> 00:49:53,920
groans, screams, moans.

1243
00:49:53,920 --> 00:49:57,280
And as the door swings up, unless you stop it.

1244
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:59,519
Yeah, no, I slam it shut.

1245
00:49:59,519 --> 00:50:01,160
It goes silent.

1246
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:04,039
Oh, this is a bad room.

1247
00:50:04,639 --> 00:50:07,800
You look behind you and the door you entered is gone.

1248
00:50:07,800 --> 00:50:08,800
Of course it is.

1249
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:11,400
Okay, well that door's not there anymore.

1250
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:16,400
Ah, is there like a keyhole I can peek my peeper through?

1251
00:50:17,160 --> 00:50:21,000
Flint and Mannix, you see the door slowly open,

1252
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:24,559
you hear that sound and then it slams shut.

1253
00:50:24,559 --> 00:50:26,840
You look down and the two figures,

1254
00:50:26,840 --> 00:50:28,760
there's like question marks above their heads,

1255
00:50:28,760 --> 00:50:31,760
exclamation marks, and they're looking at each other,

1256
00:50:31,760 --> 00:50:33,800
waving arms in the air.

1257
00:50:33,800 --> 00:50:35,760
Like we just don't care.

1258
00:50:35,760 --> 00:50:36,600
Just don't care.

1259
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:42,960
Sorry, I'm just looking to see if I have like,

1260
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:46,840
silence or if I have something, I don't think I do, but.

1261
00:50:46,840 --> 00:50:50,320
I cast Flaming Sphere and I'm just like,

1262
00:50:50,320 --> 00:50:51,320
holding onto it.

1263
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:54,120
Okay.

1264
00:50:54,120 --> 00:50:55,880
I'd like to, can I ready in action

1265
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:59,320
if this door opens up and things start coming at me?

1266
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:02,200
Can I throw a Flaming Sphere at them?

1267
00:51:02,200 --> 00:51:03,400
Yeah, because Flaming Sphere,

1268
00:51:03,400 --> 00:51:05,160
you can move on each of your turns, right?

1269
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:06,000
Yeah, absolutely.

1270
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:07,960
Yeah, you can have it readied.

1271
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:09,600
I want it ready.

1272
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:12,000
In the image, Flint and Mannix,

1273
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:14,120
you see just this flaming ball

1274
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:17,160
pop up beside Yenbul and Thea.

1275
00:51:17,160 --> 00:51:21,160
Is it just like a brighter space in their world?

1276
00:51:22,520 --> 00:51:23,520
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1277
00:51:23,520 --> 00:51:26,720
Hopefully they learn their lesson with the moonbeam.

1278
00:51:27,920 --> 00:51:28,760
Time will tell.

1279
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:30,600
I guess we'll see.

1280
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:31,480
Okay.

1281
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:34,440
All right, let's try this again.

1282
00:51:34,440 --> 00:51:35,480
Are you ready?

1283
00:51:36,679 --> 00:51:38,840
I'm gonna take some like,

1284
00:51:38,840 --> 00:51:40,880
little scraps of fabric or something

1285
00:51:40,880 --> 00:51:43,039
and maybe shove them in my ears a little bit

1286
00:51:43,039 --> 00:51:45,280
so it's a bit less cacophonous.

1287
00:51:45,280 --> 00:51:46,119
Sure.

1288
00:51:46,119 --> 00:51:47,840
I wanna do that too.

1289
00:51:47,840 --> 00:51:49,840
You are allowed to do anything, yep.

1290
00:51:51,039 --> 00:51:51,880
Anything?

1291
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:52,719
No.

1292
00:51:52,719 --> 00:51:53,559
You're not allowed to do anything with it.

1293
00:51:53,559 --> 00:51:54,639
I've removed my ears.

1294
00:51:54,639 --> 00:51:55,480
Yes.

1295
00:51:57,039 --> 00:51:59,039
In the image, you see them put in like,

1296
00:51:59,039 --> 00:52:01,119
big plugs into their ears.

1297
00:52:01,719 --> 00:52:03,079
Like comedic size.

1298
00:52:03,079 --> 00:52:05,599
I kinda look at Mannix and say like,

1299
00:52:05,599 --> 00:52:07,440
yay, nay, what do you think?

1300
00:52:07,440 --> 00:52:08,960
For going through the door

1301
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:11,359
or putting big plugs in our ears?

1302
00:52:11,359 --> 00:52:12,639
I mean, both, I guess.

1303
00:52:12,639 --> 00:52:15,000
Yeah, I mean, I don't have any of that size.

1304
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:15,839
I don't know where it,

1305
00:52:15,839 --> 00:52:19,359
maybe it's specific to their realm,

1306
00:52:19,359 --> 00:52:20,839
but I don't know.

1307
00:52:22,279 --> 00:52:24,440
I don't know if there's any right answer.

1308
00:52:26,039 --> 00:52:28,799
There's no door behind us anymore.

1309
00:52:28,799 --> 00:52:31,079
Yeah, I guess just get ready.

1310
00:52:31,920 --> 00:52:33,360
They grip their mace a little tighter

1311
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:35,920
and move towards the door.

1312
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:38,119
The door opens, the sound comes back.

1313
00:52:38,119 --> 00:52:40,960
It's muffled for Yimbo and Thea.

1314
00:52:42,199 --> 00:52:46,559
And inside, you open the door

1315
00:52:46,559 --> 00:52:48,960
and step out onto a ledge.

1316
00:52:50,199 --> 00:52:52,000
The ledge goes around the perimeter

1317
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,840
of this square room,

1318
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:59,039
but what catches your eye is the pit below you.

1319
00:53:01,079 --> 00:53:03,360
Filled with undead.

1320
00:53:04,639 --> 00:53:07,920
There are hulking orcs,

1321
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:11,440
skeletons, zombies,

1322
00:53:11,440 --> 00:53:13,159
wights,

1323
00:53:13,159 --> 00:53:17,000
banshees wailing in the distance.

1324
00:53:18,239 --> 00:53:20,239
And in the center of this room,

1325
00:53:20,239 --> 00:53:23,440
you see a pillar that comes up.

1326
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:25,480
And on top of that pillar

1327
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:29,039
is a cage with a figure in the center.

1328
00:53:30,039 --> 00:53:33,039
Who's huddled,

1329
00:53:33,039 --> 00:53:36,039
has her fingers in her ears.

1330
00:53:36,039 --> 00:53:39,039
And you see before you in this cage,

1331
00:53:39,039 --> 00:53:41,039
Yimbo.

1332
00:54:00,039 --> 00:54:02,039
The song Nowhere Land is by Kavin MacLeod

1333
00:54:02,039 --> 00:54:05,039
of incompetech.filmmusic.io.

